               <head>Valad'namah of Sultan Valad</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Valad'nāmah by Sulṭān Valad</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n87840403 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129656 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002005579" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3870-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658613.0x000001 viaf_66900471">Sulṭān Valad</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658613.0x000001 viaf_66900471">سلطان ولد</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21899">Valad'nāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21899">ولد نامه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Early near-complete manuscript of a hagiographic masnavi, incorrectly labelled here as <title>Rabāb'nāmah</title>, also known as the <title>Ibtidāʾ'nāmah</title>, written in imitation of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_98930150" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n81059876" role="ant">Rumi</persName>'s <title>Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī</title>
                        </p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning and end</p>
                        <p>Script: early scholarly <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">naskh</term>
                        </p>
                        <p>Text corresponds with another BL copy. Opening (f. 1r) corresponds to Delhi Persian 1263, f. 6v, line 7, columns 3-4. Ending (f. 237v) corresponds to Delhi Persian 1263, f. 101r, line 4, columns 3-4</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
